<br>
Problem : <br>
<br>
The pets have a large hit radius. This means that you or the tank will have to go closer to the mob than the pet to hit it. The mob will then attack you instead of the pet. You often drop melee alltogether, since you cannot take much hits anyway.<br>
<br>
At the same time, you sometimes have a non-healer group, giving the tank a big downtime. At the same time, your pets heals very fast (water). Thus you want your pet to tank! Even if you have a healer in the group! <br>
<br>
<br>
How to do it : <br>
<br>
a) park your pet in a safe spot.<br>
b) pull to the pet, so that the mob stops on TOP of your pet.<br>
<br>
If you can pull with a DD spell from where you stand, be sure to have the pet right in front of you when the mob is incoming.<br>
<br>
If you run to the mob, and pull with a spell, running back, be sure to run THROUGH pet, and stop right behind it.<br>
<br>
Problems : <br>
<br>
a) some mobs are intelligent. They go for you or the PC tank anyways. Avoid attacking these mobs, choose a “dumb” mob instead.<br>
<br>
b) If the mob hits you with melee or spell while incoming, the pet will take off to meet the mob, since you are in danger. The pet will hit the mob from max radius, not allowing you to use this tactic. This can be a problem if the mob is a spellcaster. If you are hit by a spell, your pet charges in. <br>
<br>
This can be solved by pulling with a long range DD, or selecting a non-casting mob.<br>
<br>
c) mobs have various hit ranges. The larger the range, the further behind the pet you must stop, to allow the mob to park on top of the pet. Easy to learn the various mob ranges, not a big problem.<br>
<br>
<br>
Benefits of above tactic : <br>
<br>
a) you can melee safely behind your pet. At lower levels this means a lot of extra damage.<br>
b) your group can all melee behind the pet without taking damage.<br>
c) if you do not have a healer in the group, the melee can still dish out their damage without the downtime of healing.<br>
d) if you tank with a fire pet, its great damageshield (lvl+2) will take full effect. <br>
e) the water pet heals 4% per tic at low levels. From lvl 39(?) it heals MUCH faster also. This means VERY LITTLE downtime between pulls!<br>
f) safety. If the opponent is stronger than you thought, the pet can be sacrificed while the group runs. That is not so easy if your warrior friend is the one left behind! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Finally, I think a 2h staff got a better range than a dagger, so choose the weapon for the occasion.<br>
